org.codice.ddf.configuration.migration

Interface ConfigurationMigrationService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConfigurationMigrationManager

    public interface ConfigurationMigrationService
    Service that provides a way to migrate configurations from one instance of DDF to another. This includes exporting and importing of configurations.

    This code is experimental. While this interface is functional and tested, it may change or be removed in a future version of the library.

      • doExport

        MigrationReport doExport(Path exportDirectory,
                         Consumer<MigrationMessage> consumer)
        Exports configurations to the specified path.

        Note: This version of the doExport() method will callback the provided consumer every time a migration message is recorded. The message will also be recorded with the report returned at the completion of the operation.

        Parameters:
        exportDirectory - path to export configurations to
        consumer - a consumer to call whenever a new migration message is recorded during the operation
        Returns:
        a migration report for the export operation
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if exportDirectory or consumer is null
